# Yugipedia workflow — keep main and develop in sync

`.github/workflows/import-catalog-yugipedia.yml` must be **the same file** on `main` and `develop`.

## Why

- GitHub Actions lists workflows from the **default branch (`main`)**.
- App code and workflow edits usually land on **`develop`** first.
- If the two branches diverge on this file, Actions can run an outdated workflow definition.

## When editing

After changing `import-catalog-yugipedia.yml` on either branch:

1. Commit on the branch where you made the edit (usually `develop`).
2. Sync the file to the other branch **without merging the full app**.
3. Confirm they match:

```powershell
git fetch origin
git diff origin/main origin/develop -- .github/workflows/import-catalog-yugipedia.yml
```

No output = in sync.

## Sync workflow file to main (workflow-only)

Use this when the canonical edit is on `develop` and `main` only needs the YAML:

```powershell
git fetch origin
git checkout main
git pull origin main
git checkout origin/develop -- .github/workflows/import-catalog-yugipedia.yml
git commit -m "ci: sync Yugipedia import workflow from develop"
git push origin main
git checkout develop
```

## Do not

- Merge all of `develop` into `main` just to update this workflow.
- Leave `main` with a different version after editing the workflow on `develop`.
- Assume pushing to `develop` alone updates what appears in the Actions UI.

## Optional

`import-catalog-ygoprodeck.yml` follows the same pattern if it is changed.
